23/02/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Foreign Minister Mihai Razvan Ungureanu begins a two-day visit to Germany on Wednesday (23 February).
Ungureanu will meet with German counterpart Joschka Fischer and with leaders of the main parties in parliament.
In other news, the largest association of foreign businesses in Romania, the Foreign Investors' Council, is urging the government to step up activities for macroeconomic development.
The Council notes that foreign investments in Romania stood at 53 euros per capita last year -- eight times lower than in Slovenia.
(Rompres - 23/02/05)
